.TH FASTBASE64 1 "March 2026" "simdutf" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fastbase64 \- base64 encode/decode data and print to standard output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fastbase64
[\fIOPTIONS\fR...] [\fIINPUTFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fastbase64
encodes or decodes base64 data using the high-performance simdutf library.
By default, it decodes base64 input to binary output. On large files,
it can be several times faster than standard base64 tools.
If a second filename is provided, it is used as the output file.
Otherwise, output goes to standard output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-break \fINUM\fR
Break encoded output into lines of length \fINUM\fR (default 0, meaning no breaks).
.TP
.B \-w \fNUM\fR
Same as \fB\-b\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-wrap=\fINUM\fR
Same as \fB\-b\fR.
.TP
.B \-d, \-D, \-\-decode
Decode input (default).
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-encode
Encode input.
.TP
.B \-\-ignore\-garbage
When decoding, ignore non-alphabet characters.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-input \fIFILE\fR
Input file (default: "-" for stdin; compatible with BSD/macOS base64).
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fIFILE\fR
Output file (default: "-" for stdout).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Output version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Encode a file:
.B fastbase64 \-e myfile.txt
.TP
Decode base64 data:
.B fastbase64 < encoded.txt
.TP
Encode with line wrapping:
.B fastbase64 \-e \-w 76 myfile.txt
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR base64 (1),
.BR iconv (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by the simdutf development team.